## Resolution 2015-08-05.jdd.1: Diversity Scholarships for FLOSS conferences

<pre>
WHEREAS

1. The corporation recognizes the value of supporting a diverse technical
community

2. The corporation recognizes that education about Free and Open Source
software is a core requirement for increasing the user base of said
software

THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

1. That a scholarship program for diversity will help strengthen our
community

1. The board shall budget 5000.00 USD for the fourth calendar quarter of
2015 (October 1st - December 31st)

2. The board shall budget an additional 5,000.00 USD for each calendar
quarter in 2016

3. The respective budgets shall be used for travel and attendance costs to
approved conferences

4. Receivers of the scholarship must fit a diversity profile

5. The board will create and publicly publish an application process no
later than September 30th, 2015.

5. Applicants for the scholarship must be 18 years old or older, and must
belong to a group that is underrepresented in the technology industry.
This includes, but is not limited to people who identify as women, African
American, Hispanic, LGBTQ, low-income, and people with disabilities who
may not otherwise have the opportunity to attend a FLOSS conference.
</pre>


